<div class="container-fluid py-5 wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.1s">
    <div class="container py-5">
        <div class="row g-5">
            <div class="col-lg-7">
                <div class="section-title position-relative pb-3 mb-5">
                    <h5 class="fw-bold text-primary text-uppercase"></h5>
                    <h1 class="mb-0">Hybrid Mobile App Devleopment</h1>
                </div>
                <p class="mb-4">
                    Hybrid app development involves creating mobile applications that combine web technologies like HTML, CSS, and JavaScript with native code. These apps are typically built using frameworks like Apache Cordova, Ionic, or PhoneGap, which allow developers to write code once and deploy it across multiple platforms. By leveraging web technologies, hybrid apps offer advantages such as faster development cycles, lower costs, and easier maintenance compared to native apps. Additionally, hybrid apps can access device features through plugins, providing a level of functionality similar to native apps. However, hybrid apps may face performance limitations compared to native apps, as they run within a web view container. Despite this, hybrid app development remains a popular choice for businesses seeking to reach a broad audience across different platforms efficiently.
                </p>



            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-5" style="min-height: 500px;">
                <div class="position-relative h-100">
